<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: ON CUSTER'S TRAIL 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By SYD KEARNEY 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
SOUTH DAKOTA 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The 73,000-acre Custer State Park is located in the southwest
corner of the state. Bison, elk, pronghorn antelope and bighorn
sheep are among residents. Activities include hiking, fishing,
swimming, biking, rock climbing, horseback riding and Jeep tours.
Lodging ranges from camping to a historical lodge. Call
605-255-4515.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mount Rushmore National Memorial is located 25 miles southwest
of Rapid City, S.D. The park is open daily, except Christmas Day.
Admission is free, but the parking fee is $8 per vehicle. Call
605-574-2523; access www.nps.gov on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   _ For information on attractions, lodging and special events in
South Dakota, call 800-732-5682; access www.travelsd.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; WYOMING &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ Devils Tower National Monument rises 1,267 feet above the
northeastern Wyoming prairie. The park is open daily. Admission is
free, but the parking fee is $8 per vehicle. Camping is available.
Call 307-467-5283; access www.nps.gov.
</P>
<P>
   Fort Phil Kearny State Historic Site is located 20 miles south
of Sheridan, Wyo. A visitors center offers exhibits, a bookstore
and brochures detailing self-guided tours of the fort and two
nearby battlefields. The park is closed December through March.
Admission is $1 per person. Call 307-684-7629; access
http://commerce.state.wy.us/sphs/kearny1.htm.
</P>
<P>
   For information on attractions, lodging and special events in
Wyoming, call 800-225-5996; access www.wyomingtourism.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; MONTANA &LR;  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Little Bighorn Battlefield National Monument is located 65 miles
east-southeast of Billings, Mont. Custer National Cemetery is
located within the park. The park is open year-round. Admission is
$6 per vehicle; pedestrians and private tours are subject to a
charge of $3 per person. Call 406-638-2621; access www.nps.gov.
</P>
<P>
   For information on attractions, lodging and special events in
Montana, call 800-847-4868; access www.visitmt.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
