<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: LUCERNE AND LONDON 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By HARRY SHATTUCK 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
LUCERNE 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Carnival: The Lucerne Carnival begins before dawn on the
Thursday before Ash Wednesday. (Ash Wednesday is March 8, 2000.)
Lucerne's 2000 celebration is scheduled March 2-7, with parades
planned March 2, 6 and 7.
</P>
<P>
   Many other Swiss Carnival celebrations take place after Lent
begins, a Protestant reaction to Catholicism. Basel's Carnival, the
nation's biggest with more than 20,000 masked participants, begins
at 4 a.m. March 13 next year and continues through the evening of
March 15.
</P>
<P>
   Italian-speaking communities in southern Switzerland's Ticino
region celebrate Carnival in a different fashion. In a tradition
dating to the 1860s, risotto feasts are the highlight on Shrove
Tuesday (Mardi Gras Day, March 7, 2000).
</P>
<P>
   Rail passes: Rail Europe offers a multitude of travel passes
that focus specifically on Switzerland or include other European
countries. A four-day Swiss Pass costs $136 per person in second
class or $208 in first class when two or more people travel
together. Children under 16 travel free with a parent. Swiss Passes
for unlimited travel covering 8, 15 or 21 consecutive days or one
month also are available.
</P>
<P>
   Call 888-382-7245. Access www.raileurope.com on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   Additional information: For information about lodging, dining,
attractions and events in Lucerne, access www.luzern.org. Also
helpful is www.lucerne.ch. Among the city's most popular
attractions is the Swiss Transport Museum; access
www.verkehrshaus.ch.
</P>
<P>
   The Lucerne International Festival of Music is one of Europe's
premier annual events; the 2000 festival is Aug. 17-Sept. 16.
Access www.lucernemusic.ch for program details.
</P>
<P>
   A good source within the United States for information about
Lucerne or any other Swiss destination is Switzerland Tourism. Call
212-757-5944; or access www.myswitzerland.com or
www.discover-switzerland.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
LONDON &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Theaters: A good online source for London theater listings and
news is www.playbill.com. Individual theaters' offerings and ticket
information are included.
</P>
<P>
   Additional information: For recommendations on lodging, dining,
major attractions and events, the London Tourist Board operates a
comprehensive Web site at www.londontown.com; that site also
devotes a section to the theater. The Evening Standard newspaper's
online service also is helpful: Access www.thisislondon.com. For
free brochures and tourist information about all of Britain,
including London, call the British Tourist Authority at
800-462-2748. Access www.visitbritain.com on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
