   WITH: TRAVEL BRIEFS -- Amtrak and the Hertz Corp. are expanding
efforts to help railroad passengers rent cars on arrival, just as
air passengers can at the airport. (N.Y. Times News Service.)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-SAVANNAH _ SAVANNAH, Ga. _ Forget chestnuts roasting on
an open fire, Jack Frost nipping at your nose. And don't even think
about folks dressed up like Eskimos. In this historic coastal city,
signs that the holidays have arrived are a bit more subtle. Not
icicles, but Spanish moss drips from ancient live oaks, and the
city's version of the Rockefeller Center ice rink is inside. Still,
Savannah seems a fine place to find some holiday spirit. (Thrasher,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). with Photos and Layout.
