 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
Portable e-mail units handy 
By James Cummings  
c.1999 Cox News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Not everybody who wants to send and receive
e-mail wants or needs a personal computer. It's possible to have
e-mail with a device that connects to phone lines and a service
that provides e-mail access only.
</P>
<P>
   VTech Industries of Wheeling, Ill., sells several e-mail
products that it says can be used anywhere by simply plugging them
into a telephone jack. Two of the products, e-Mail PostBox and
e-Mail Express, sell for less than $100.
</P>
<P>
   The e-Mail Express is designed to be very portable. It measures
6.3-by-3.5 inches and weighs about 7 ounces. It's compact size
limits the size of the keyboard and the LCD viewing screen,
however, so it may be somewhat uncomfortable for some people to
use.
</P>
<P>
   The e-Mail Express has an address book and calendar and can save
up to 500 messages. It has a ``Smart Dialer'' feature that ensures
you get a local phone rate no matter where you're calling from.
</P>
<P>
   It also has filters to block e-mail you don't want. The device
can be set to accept e-mails only from a list of known senders, so
you won't be flooded with advertisements, and parents can protect
children from receiving adult material.
</P>
<P>
   The e-Mail PostBox is a desktop model with a few more features
than e-Mail Express. It has a full-size keyboard, but it's still
compact at about 2.2 pounds and 12.4 by 8.2 inches. It also has a
larger LCD screen _ eight lines of 40 characters _ than the e-Mail
Express, which has five lines of 40 characters.
</P>
<P>
   The e-Mail PostBox supports up to five individual e-mail
accounts, each with its own calendar, address book and memo pad.
</P>
<P>
   VTech sells e-Mail Express for $79.99 and e-Mail PostBox for
$99.99 only by phone or online. To order call (888) 468-8324
(GO-VTECH) or log on at www.vtechworld.com.
</P>
<P>
   VTech also supplies the e-mail service for its devices. The
service costs $24.99 a quarter or $89.99 a year. To sign up you
must have a credit card, and service charges will be deducted from
your credit card account until you cancel the service.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
