</P>
<P>
   ..............OO..OO..OO..OO..OO..............
</P>
<P>
   HAPPY THANKSGIVING? A NATIVE-AMERICAN PERSPECTIVE
</P>
<P>
   ``Like it or not, American Indians are forever tied to the
Thanksgiving holiday,'' writes Native-American Karen Lincoln
Michel. ``Occasionally, around this time of year, some non-Indian
will smile at me and say something like: `There would be no
Thanksgiving if it wasn't for your people.' That's right. If tribes
hadn't shown white folks the ropes, we'd probably give thanks each
day that we still had our land.''
</P>
<P>
   ..............OO..OO..OO..OO..OO..............
</P>
<P>
   ............OO...OO...OO...OO...OO............
