<HEADER>
A0443 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-VIDEO-GIANT25-COX     11-24 0195
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-GIANT25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Video of the week
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   `The Iron Giant' (PG)
</P>
<P>
   It's a shame to see kids swamping theaters playing that
buy-the-collectibles extravaganza ``Pokemon: The First Movie,''
while Warner Bros. couldn't get an audience for this smart and
sweet animated feature. It's one of the summer's overlooked gems.
</P>
<P>
   Based on British poet Ted Hughes' book, but transferred to Cold
War America of the 1950s, it's the tale of a young boy who
befriends the titular man-machine. The big guy has fallen from the
sky but doesn't seem to know his mission. Is he as gentle as he
seems, or programmed for a darker purpose?
</P>
<P>
   The movie mixes comedy, action and an animation style that's
definitely not Disney, but has a jazzy style all its own. Speaking
of Disney, you don't get songs and adorable sidekicks, but a
bittersweet tale of friendship that gives adults in the room as
much to enjoy as their kids. Priced to buy: $22.95 VHS, $24.98 DVD.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
