greatest challenge is to reach school age without becoming infected
or being directly affected by HIV.
</P>
<P>
   South Africa has the fastest growing rates of HIV in the world
and, consequently, the most alarming prognosis for the next
generation. Already 20 percent of the work force is estimated to be
infected with HIV.
</P>
<P>
   In six years' time there are expected to be one million AIDS
