A0483 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX     11-24 0602
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE RECIPE FOR BECOMING `BEST MOM IN THE WORLD'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Myself, and most importantly my son Alex, would love the
recipe for Luby's macaroni and cheese. Please find time and space
to print this recipe soon so I can be voted `The Best Mom in the
World,' '' writes Janet Bryant of Crowley, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   No problem; that recipe is printed in ``Luby's Cafeteria 50th
Anniversary Recipe Collection,'' which is sold at all Luby's.
</P>
<P>
   LUBY'S MACARONI AND CHEESE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces (2 cups) dry elbow macaroni
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons nonfat dry milk
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon butter or margarine, melted
</P>
<P>
   1 1/4 cups boiling water
</P>
<P>
   3 cups (12 ounces) shredded American cheese
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
</P>
<P>
   Heat oven to 350 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   In large bowl, mix dry milk, flour and butter. Gradually add
boiling water, beating constantly. Add 1 1/2 cups of the cheese and
continue beating until smooth and creamy. Stir in macaroni, 1 cup
of the remaining cheese, and salt. Transfer to lightly greased
2-quart baking dish. Cover with foil.
</P>
<P>
   Bake 25 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Remove foil. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Continue
baking 1 minute or until cheese melts.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 271 calories, 12 grams fat, 27
grams carbohydrates, 13 grams protein, 28 milligrams cholesterol,
611 milligrams sodium, 41 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   It's apple season: In response to our reader who wants a recipe
for fresh apple cake, here's one that ran in a Washington
newspaper. It was created by writer Linda Bryant Smith.
</P>
<P>
   LINDA'S FRESH APPLE CAKE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 9
</P>
<P>
   3 eggs
</P>
<P>
   1 cup brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup canola oil
</P>
<P>
   2 cups flour
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon nutmeg
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   3 Golden Delicious apples, cored and chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 cup nuts, chopped and divided
</P>
<P>
   Beat eggs, sugar and oil until no lumps remain. Add flour,
baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in apples and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread batter in a 9-inch baking pan that has been greased.
Sprinkle remaining nuts over the top. Bake at 325 degrees about 60
minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 525 calories, 29 grams fat, 64
grams carbohydrates, 6 grams protein, 71 milligrams cholesterol,
252 milligrams sodium, 50 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Everett Herald''
</P>
<P>
   Requests:
</P>
