<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following business
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, Nov. 25 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   GENTLE-GIANT (Burbank, Calif.) _ Every action figure, toothpaste
holder and pencil topper tied to ``Toy Story 2'' has its own story,
beginning in an obscure facility called Gentle Giant Inc. By Jason
Takenouchi. (Will move in the ``f'' financial wires.)
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-EATS (Los Angeles) _ Warner Bros. is allowing the
re-creation of studio setsfrom four of its films _ ``Gold Diggers
of 1939,'' ``Casablanca,'' ``Ocean's 11'' and ``Batman'' _ for the
WB Stage 16 eatery at the Venetian in Las Vegas. By Dave McNary.
(Will move in the ``f'' financial wires.)
</P>
<P>
   UNIVERSAL-STUDIOS (Los Angeles) _ Universal Studios is
considering a program to eliminate long lines at its most popular
rides. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial wires.)
</P>
