<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THEY WANT TO MAKE YOU AN EXTRA
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ How can I find a list of film productions that might be
in the market for extras in the area? _ J.P., Fort Worth, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ To find movies and TV shows looking for extras, call
the Dallas Fort Worth Regional Film Commission at (972) 234-5697
and the Texas Film Commission production hot line at (512)
463-7799.
</P>
<P>
   One current opportunity is the Robert Altman movie ``Dr. T and
the Women,'' which is filming in Dallas through January. Send a
photo, day and evening phone numbers and information about yourself
to Dr. T Extras, Barbara Blanchette, Box 551383, Dallas, TX 75355.
</P>
<P>
   The CBS series ``Walker, Texas Ranger'' often needs extras.
Write to Extras Department, 13801 Diplomat, Farmers Branch, TX
75234.
</P>
<P>
   Being an extra often requires a full-day schedule and an ability
to ``sit around and wait a lot,'' said Ellen Mayers, assistant
director of the film commission. ``I was an extra in `Split Image.'
It was possibly the most boring three days of my life, but somehow
fascinating at the same time.''
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Where can I write to join the Lucille Ball fan club? _
R.L., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Write to the We Love Lucy Fan Club, Box 56234, Sherman
Oaks, CA 91413-1234; or visit the World Wide Web site
www.lucyfan.com.
</P>
<P>
   Members pay $28 to receive ``Lucyfan Magazine,'' a photo, lapel
pin and details about the ``Loving Lucy'' convention, which
attracts more than 1,000 people each year.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
