<HEADLINE>
JETS' FERGUSON IS SUSPENDED 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. _ Jason Ferguson, the Jets' nose guard, was
suspended Wednesday for four games by the National Football League
for testing positive for steroids.
</P>
<P>
   Ferguson is the first Jet to be suspended for violating the
league's policy on performance-enhancing drugs. He tested positive
for marijuana at the 1997 combine, which dropped him to the seventh
round.
</P>
<P>
   After he was drafted, Ferguson was contrite, saying he was sorry
that he had embarrassed his mother. The Jets had no statement on
the matter Wednesday, with neither Coach Bill Parcells nor Ferguson
available for a comment.
</P>
<P>
   Ferguson sprained a knee in the season opener and missed the
next three games. The Jets lost two of those games; since his
return, the team has won three and lost two, surrendering more than
20 points just once.
</P>
</TEXT>
