<SLUG> BC-RESEARCH-ALLIANCE-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UNIVERSITY AND RESEARCH INSTITUTE FORM ALLIANCE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JULIUS A. KARASH  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ The University of Kansas and the Midwest
Research Institute have formed an alliance to promote joint
research projects and other collaborative efforts.
</P>
<P>
   The KUMRI Alliance will focus on pharmaceuticals, biomedical
engineering and information technology, officials with the two
institutions said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Given KU's strength in basic and clinical research and MRI's
expertise in applied research, this partnership is a great fit,''
KU Chancellor Robert Hemenway said in a news release. ``KUMRI will
be financially beneficial to both institutions.''
</P>
<P>
   James Spigarelli, MRI's chief operating officer, said the
alliance would break new ground in cooperative research between the
institutions.
</P>
<P>
   The Kansas City-based Midwest Research Institute is an
independent, nonprofit organization that performs contract research
for business, industry and government.
</P>
<P>
   The KU-MRI collaboration is occurring amid heightened interest
in research and joint research projects in the Kansas City area.
</P>
<P>
   Much of that heightened interest has been generated by the
Stowers Institute for Medical Research, which is to begin work
about a year from now. Area leaders are looking to the Stowers
Institute as a catalyst to turn Kansas City into one of the
nation's top 10 biomedical research and development sites.
</P>
<P>
   KU and the University of Missouri-Kansas City recently announced
a joint initiative in life sciences research and education.
</P>
<P>
   KU and MRI have collaborated on clinical research projects
related to smoking cessation, cancer prevention, chemotherapy and
anti-estrogen drugs.
</P>
<P>
   The goals of the alliance include:
</P>
<P>
   - Promoting joint research projects and other collaborations.
</P>
<P>
   - Establishing a database of common capabilities for KU and MRI
researchers.
</P>
<P>
   - Coordinating seminars and other activities that promote
collaborations and the exchange of ideas.
</P>
<P>
   - Creating mechanisms to allow sharing of equipment and
services.
</P>
<P>
   - Creating joint appointments, internships and postdoctoral
fellowships.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
